    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "RE: FLYING DISCS SIGHTED BY [REDACTED] b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "[REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "TACOMA, WASHINGTON",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "SM - X",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "Dear Sir:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "The following, in general, are the facts regarding the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "flying disc story that started by [REDACTED] which",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "subsequently resulted in news stories by the Tacoma Times, the Boise Statesman b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "and the Chicago Times that a B-25 carrying Army Intelligence officers was shot",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "down or sabotaged over Kelso, Washington on August 1, 1947 because it was carry-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "ing some flying disc fragments.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "The original story, as related by [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "[REDACTED] was to the effect that [REDACTED] while patrolling in his boat near Maury",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "Island, Washington, sighted six flying discs, one of which fluttered to the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "earth and disintegrated, showering his boat with fragments which caused some",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "damage to the boat and killed his dog. [REDACTED] wrote a letter to [REDACTED] b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "[REDACTED] of Ziff-Davis Company which publishes fantastic adventure magazines in",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "Chicago, sending him fragments of the flying disk and relating the above story.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "[REDACTED] requested Trans-Radio News in Chicago to verify the story as related",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "by [REDACTED] [REDACTED] telegraphed [REDACTED] confirming [REDACTED] story.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "[REDACTED] then engaged [REDACTED] Boise, Idaho, who was the first to report",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "sighting the flying disc and whom [REDACTED] had previously made a contract for",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "a story regarding the flying disc, to come to Tacoma and check the story as",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "related by [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "[REDACTED] came to Tacoma, Washington July 30, 1947 and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "arranged for a meeting the following day, July 31, with [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "[REDACTED] in his room 502, Winthrop Hotel, Tacoma, Washington. [REDACTED] also b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "called to attend the meeting [REDACTED] United Airlines Pilot who",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "had also reported seeing flying disc fragments, and Army Intelligence to attend",
